   <td> <table width=95%><tr><td class=headings valign="bottom"><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/bmithanielmarrdailynews>Mithaniel Marr Daily News</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11>Other Rants-n-Flames</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;> Last post - and my editorial on Verant. (Long)</td><td align=right valign="bottom"><a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/march/newtopic.gif border=0 alt="New Topic"></a>  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=864.topic><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/march/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a>  </td></tr><tr><td align=left><br>Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showMessageRange?topicID=864.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right> <br> <a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=864.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showNextMessage?topicID=864.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#DEEFDE class=headings><font color=#006400>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#DEEFDE class=headings><font color=#006400>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uutnayan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utnayan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Eventempered<br>Retired MMDN Admin</span><br>  Posts: 969<br> <font color=#006400>(9/25/01 10:33:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=864.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Last post - and my editorial on Verant. (Long)</span><hr size=1> I have been here as an admin, as a player, guiding on another server for 1.5 years.  In that time I have seen a lot of Everquest.  A lot of playtime.  Lots of classes. Lots of idiots. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LOTS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of wanna be's. <br>
<br>
But in the end, it is my opinion that the game revolves around the company that makes it.  Now since this is my last post, I would like to make it more of a nice editorial, without any flames.  <br>
<br>
Everquest is a solid game.  If it wasn't, I would not have played for so long.  Anyone that says Everquest sucks after they leave the game is lying.  I think most people think that the company of &quot;Verant&quot; sucks.  Not the game.  From my perspective, It is the company which is terrible. <br>
<br>
I will touch on a few key points, which will be:<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Verant's Consistency</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The lies from Verant</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The so called end game</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
And last but not least... <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The carrot in front of the running bunny</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The single player. Anyone here.  You have a problem, you are worried.  You spend a huge amount of time in game on a quest, or a mob, or your characters reputation in general. My examples of how much Verant cares for the average player. <br>
<br>
Dextor: Spends about 5 months amount of time obtaining his epic. After he gets all the pieces, accidentally and without thinking, turns the items into a wrong mob.  He petitions.  He says that there is nothing they can do as he &quot;Failed&quot; the quest. <br>
<br>
How can you fail the quest when you have gotten everyone together, planned effortlessly, and made ONE single mistake by giving the items to the wrong NPC.  Which the NPC should have said &quot;What will I do with this?&quot; and give the items back.  Like in any RPG I have played out there to this date. <br>
<br>
Verant here not only lost a player, but a Senior Guide.  Dextor put a huge amount of time into this game, and ifyou know what effort it takes to be a senior guide, than you know how much he gave this company as well.  He knew the rules, knew what he had been trained to say himself, but when it happened to him he realized the gravity of the moment, and noticed the lack of compassion by Verant.  Obviously thinking he was so hooked on the game he would spend another 5 months getting the items. He left EQ and he left helping others on his guide server.  Did Verant care?  Not one bit. <br>
<br>
But more importantly, was in my guiding days.  I was a Guide since March of 2000. Generation 69 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  woot. <br>
<br>
I took a petition about 2 months later.  Exact and to the T of what happened to Dextor.  Except, he was a rogue and handed in his items to the wrong character.  I told him there wasn't anything we could do, I escalated the petition by request to the head GM.  A day later I saw him with a Ragebringer.  I asked the GM how this happened and he said &quot;I felt sorry for him&quot;. <br>
<br>
Where was this compassion with Dextor? How about with me? <br>
<br>
When someone impersonated my character, and the person in question never bothered to look at the guild tag to see who it was.  The person said he was me and asked to borrow a guildmates Fungi Tunic.  I logged in to complete shock with everyone teling me I should give back an item I never had. <br>
<br>
I log to chat to grab a chat GM. Which normally I know the routine.  Let the server GM handle it.  Well, I didn't know who the hell the new server GM was as Mith Marr has changed over 2-3 times in the last 2 months.  I logged in as my player, and was ignored by the GM in tells and in says. Over and over.  Not even a response saying &quot;Let the head GM on your server handle it&quot; meanwhile this person kep on answering questions. <br>
<br>
I logged into my Guide Character where I was promptly told that if I did not cease I would be removed from the guide program if I persisted to get help with my guide character.  I explained that I asked him about 5 times and he ignored me to which he replied, &quot;Tough&quot;. Honest to God. <br>
<br>
At that point I noticed the severe lack of compassion for <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Anyone</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that runs into trouble in this game. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The lies from Verant</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I can tell you right now of about 4 zones that were NOT complete upon release.  But yet when players are devoting their time to playing the game, seeing the end game, they watch as you keep playing and playing knowing you will not actually <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> reach</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> anything until they put it in.  Meanwhile, you are chasing something that DOESN'T Exist.  And they do not care. <br>
<br>
When Velious came out, the Plane of Mischief was NEVER working.  Yet you heard Abashi and Absor say &quot;It is working as intended&quot;.  People would wonder &quot;what are these cards for... it is driving me batty!&quot;.  verant kept on with their cryptic ways.  Little to be known...  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The vendor which sold the kit which combines these cards into quest items WAS NOT EVEN IN PLACE... 3 MONTHS AFTER RELEASE!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Enough said about that topic.  You just imagine players for 3 months pursuing to complete quests which are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> IMPOSSIBLE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to complete. I mean... Not just hard.  PHYSICALLY impossible. <br>
<br>
Did Verant care?  No.  They got your money for another 3 months while you had no clue about this vendor in the first place, than placed it in RV 3 months after the fact. <br>
<br>
Temple of Veeshans. Little known fact.  The loot table on the boss mobs was not completed until March. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3 Months after release.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Sleepers. How could I even argue with Verant on this one correct?  I mean its &quot;working as intended&quot; right? <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WRONG</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Look at what happened when the sleeper was woken up the first time.  A naked Human popped, meaning the mob was not even in the graphic database yet, 2 zones crashed and 2 scrips went off without anything happening.  What was done? Verant <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 5 months after release of Velious</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> buffs the 4th warder to make him unkillable, until they can patch the zone which <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> should have been fucking completed 3-4 months ago</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Notice I am giving ample time for Verant to realize there was a bug on their own if they needed to do some tests after release.  But for Christs sake, patch it before players enter the zone. <br>
<br>
What happens next?  BOTS kills the 4th after they make him killable again. Ker spawns, rampages in Skyshrine and Sleeper.  Kael and Western wastes crash. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 5 Months after release</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Afterlife does it, and I think they finally might have it right. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 6 months after release</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
<br>
Now, guilds that strive to see the end game and be the best, have this to look forward to?  They give up their RL time, sink UNIMAGINABLE amounts of time into this game for a company that could not give a rats ass. And why can I say that? Because if they had, these zones would have been tested and fixed before these guilds ever got to them.  Had they been a company that cared, they would have known the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> sickly</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> amount of time it takes to get to this end game.  <br>
<br>
But guess what FoH, AL, VM, BOTS and others.  You are not even 5% of the subscription rate.  So even you do not matter. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The bunny chasing the carrot</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Imagine a little bunny in a race chasing this moving carrot.  He will never get it.  Never be able to eat it.  You just keep chasing and chasing and chasing. <br>
<br>
There will never be an end to this game as long as you play.  It is the way with all MMORPG's, except for AO if it actually makes it through the 4 year script it planned out without going bankrupt. <br>
<br>
But the biggest thing, is chasing a carrot that isn't even there. <br>
<br>
How many people reading this are playing for the endgame.  To see it all.  To win the unwinnable.  To do the un-doable. Subjectively the end game might be for you getting the highest level, seeing all the zones, and having the best pieces of equipment the game can give you, and killing EVERY mob in the game.    That essentially is &quot;Beating&quot; the game. <br>
<br>
Will it ever come to fruition?  No.  Because at the current state no one will be able to kill the sleeper.  Seeing it DT'd for 5 minutes and not even watch the health bar move, makes it unkillable by anyone no matter how many you have. <br>
<br>
Does that make EQ bad?  Nope.  I think it is great that they are trying to add something dynamic.  But not when others are trying to fight to the same place.  <br>
<br>
Example: Unless it is changed, or the magical &quot;working as intended&quot; quest to bring back Kera to sleepers from its quest to hunt out Veeshan, a guild on Mith Marr will never be able to realize the end game of waking the sleeper for themselves. And for any other guild besides AL, what is the point of playing if you wanted to realize that goal? <br>
<br>
If it is to socialize, level, get loot, and see the zone, then you are happy.  But if you wanted to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Be a part of</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the end game, as we know it now...  You are out of luck. <br>
<br>
So at the end when Verant just took that carrot you were chasing, and fed it to the hand, think back of how you are giving your money to a company which frankly has no compassion, outlook.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Guiding</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
My experience guiding was one of the best.  I became so close to people in the guide program simply because we all wanted to make things a better place.  Albeit about 75% of the times we wanted to help we couldn't. <br>
<br>
My most memorable moment and something I will never forget, and something that brought life back to the game. <br>
<br>
The first GM on my server I encountered, Ozzmar. He was a great guy and one of the best GM's ever known. He still works for Verant but I lost track of him.  Anyhow, I took control of a 45th level shaman which was turned into a cockatrice. I was made about 75% taller than the other 3-4 birds. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Which were also guide controlled.  I was named &quot;Big Bird&quot; and others were named Polly and the like <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Was pretty hilarious.  <br>
<br>
We went around the skyfire entrance and just hung out for a while chirping and pecking... When I saw this one Necromancer which <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ALWAYS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> swore at me when I was handling his petitions.  Needless to say I nuked him in about 5 seconds flat.  The funniest thing I ever did see after was a shout from him... &quot;WTF! I just got killed by Big Bird and his posse!&quot; and the rest of the server thinking he was insane <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
You can become so close to everyone in the guide program.  I made countless friends, and believe it or not when someone left the program I would get teary eyed because I loved talking to those people. Which at the time was about 10 hours a week but was much more than that for me. <br>
<br>
Guides, Seniors, put SO much time into this game to help others.  Verant definately helps us.  They show gratitude by letting us play for free, and another benefit which I will not name because I am sure people will cry about it and get it taken away from the guides. None the less we use it for our tools. <br>
<br>
But they definately need to learn a lot about how to take care of a customer.  They need to learn alot about compassion.  I would even find myself at times being rude and short and to the point.  In Verant's eyes, the customer is always wrong.  You cannot blame them half the time, because a lot of it the people are just dumbasses.  Wanting resses for going LD and blaming the server when no one else dropped. Zoning with low life and drying not knowing the server takes a second or two to let the client know it is zoning, or vice versa, and the mob hits you for one last shot and you die. <br>
<br>
Worse yet, one I had happen to me, when you zone with 200 health and a mob is chasing you... It hits for a max of about 34 and somehow you die. And you hear that same excuse as above.  Knowing it is not possible. <br>
<br>
Bugs happen.  Zone issues happen.  Customer service issues happen.  It is one thing to notice a mistake, admit it and fix it. <br>
<br>
But it is another to leave the entire end game untouched and bugged for over 4 months. It is another thing to not help a person that spent 5 months on an epic quest to see all of it go away.  It is another thing to watch a persons reputation go down with a fake character impersonation and not care about how much time the person has invested into that character.  All because you are one $9.95 a month. And frankly, you do not matter. <br>
<br>
It is one thing to devote time to this game and have it actually be there when you get to that objective.  <br>
<br>
So my ending is, goodbye EQ, goodbye EQ message boards, and last but certainly not least, goodbye to a company which will never care about anything but the pocket book... and that is not how you retain customers.  <br>
<br>
Verant if you are reading: This is only the first game you made.  You have others coming, and no matter how much oomph you might put into the following games, people remember quite well how they were treated. <br>
<br>
And with companies from all walks of life that will throw there hat into the ring, Blizzard, Westwood, and bigger names than Verant, you should take notes on how to treat customers and players.  Because unlike 2 years ago, people now will start to have a choice.  And the only 2 things keeping them in the game will be the support they get from the company, and the content of the game. <br>
<br>
  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
 <br>
