<br>
Well Everquest has more in common with a drug addiction then it does a normal videogame.  Since I've stopped playing my life is already better.  I've been cleaning and organizing my apartment, socializing with friends, and my stress level has dropped a great deal.  I no longer have this constant mental haze hanging over me and oddly enough feel much better away from the game.<br>
<br>
I think people don't like to admit the negative aspects of becoming absorb in MMORPGs, but I think its something that will become a big problem as these games evolve into ever more complex worlds.<br>
<br>
Just wait... In a few years you'll see talkshows featuring MMORPG orphans - kids whose parents neglected them to play games like EQ.  i.e. &quot;I hate my dad! All he ever did was run off and chase half naked woodelves!&quot;.<br>
<br>
Think about it..<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
