<br>
Everquest is a great idea, everything is balanced pretty well in the game, that is why it has last so long. Sure, Verant has seemed to be lazy in the past couple of months, especially since velious came out. The reason why the game is so fun to all of you, and so addictive is because it can be so rewarding. For some people a reward is simply buying the item you always wanted to buy, or explore a new zone, chat with friends, gain a level, kill a new mob, win a lotto, etc. The thing about everquest is that it isn't easy to get what you want, that's why you keep coming back for more. I was in lguk for 10 lvls and never even saw an fbss drop, but i heard of them dropping so i kept coming back for more. <br>
<br>
I quit everquest fairly reason, I have three reasons for that.<br>
<br>
First reason is my damn hardware firewall in my modem/router. It basically caused me to be sent back to my server selection screen 2/3 of the times i zoned. This was before I figured out you can open up ports to allow information to travel freely. Anyways, this whole problem and trying to deal with 2wire, pissed me off.<br>
<br>
Secondly, Eq was becoming a little too time consuming, and a little too hectic at times, especially with the zoning problem I had. The guild I was in basically fell apart, and finals were coming up at school. The game has temperarily lost its luster.<br>
<br>
Lastly, a lot of the people in the game were getting to me. You know, the bad groupmembers, the whiners, the begging noobs, KC trainers, etc. This was something that I could deal with all 52 lvls previously, but when it added onto the zoning problem, I just gave up and quit.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I was just wondering Ut, or anyone else who is quitting, will you be trying DAoC? It looks like a great game and will be online in 2 weeks, I'm thinking of buying it if I can figure out how to open up the ports of my firewall (I'm firewall illiterate). It looks very similar to EQ when it first came out, but has an interesting PvP high lvl experience to it. In a month I will check back here and at the DAoC boards to see how people like it, and to see if it is the next EQ, or the next AO, only time will tell. Until then.... <p>Foror Against

